Lauren Perry gave birth to twins Mason and Chloe at 30 weeks . 
  She had her waters break just 23 weeks into her pregnancy . 
  Her son Mason was admitted to hospital after he contracted a flesh-eating virus . 
  Eight months later when he had his colostomy removed he contracted necrotising fasciitis . 
  He was delivered via caesarean and spent his first two months in intensive care . 
  After the surgery he nearly lost his life to the disease . 
  It perforated his bowel and ate tissue from his chest cavity . 
 